{"title_page": "Our School (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Redirect|Our School|the South Korean documentary film|Our School (film)}}\n{{more citations needed|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Our School\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Entertainment]]<br />[[Documentary]]<br />[[Reality television]]\n| creator                  = [[BBC]]\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Cher Adamson<br />Chris Chapman<br />Matt Grosch<br>Jamie McLeish\n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| voices                   = Martin\n Thoburn (Series 1 & 2017 Special, 2018 Special, 2020 Special)<br> Trevor Evans (Series 2 & 2017 Special, 2018 Special, 2020 Special)<br> Martin Jones (Series 3 & 2018 Special) Ben Shore (2019 Special & 2020 Special)<br> Ewan Nicoll (Series 4 & 2019 Special, 2020 Special)<br>[[Shirley Ballas]] (Our School Summer Camp)<br> Helena Worth (Series 5 & 2020 Special)<br> Julie Kiley (Series 6)\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \"Our School\"\n| endtheme                 = \"Our School\"\n| composer                 = Sam Gale\n| country                  = [[United Kingdom]]\n| language                 = [[English language|English]] (UK)\n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = Kez Margrie<br />Richard Marson\n| producer                 = Vanessa Singh<br />Natasha Cox<br />Matt Grosch<br />Cher Adamson<br />Chris Chapman<br />Jamie McLeish\n| location                 = [[Conyers School]] (Series 1)<br />[[Greenwood Academy, Birmingham|Greenwood Academy]] (Series 2)<br />[[Firth Park Academy]] (Series 3)<br />[[Shawlands Academy]] (Series 4)\n[[Hawthorn High School]] (Series 5)<br />[[Ryburn Valley High School]] (Series 6)\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = Samdeep Singh Rana\n| camera                   = Multi camera<br />Dual cameras\n| runtime                  = 30 minutes\n| company                  = [[Twofour|TwoFour]]\n| distributor              = TwoFour\n| network                  = [[CBBC (TV channel)|CBBC]] (2014-present) <br>[[CBBC (TV channel)#CBBC HD|CBBC HD]] (2013-present)\n| picture_format           = [[High-definition television|HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format             = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2014|09|03|df=yes}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  =\n| website                  = https://www.bbc.co.uk/cbbc/shows/our-school\n| production_website       = \n| num_series               = 6\n}}\n'''''Our School''''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[documentary]] [[reality television]] programme on [[CBBC]] which first aired on 3 September 2014 and has run for six series. It uses a [[fly on the wall]] format to show the everyday lives of the staff and pupils of secondary schools and follows children as they move from year 6 into year 7, each series is filmed in a different school.\n\n==Series overview==\n<!--Full linking is used for transclusion to main article-->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=2 rowspan=2|Series\n!rowspan=2|Episodes\n!colspan=2|Originally aired\n|-\n!First aired\n!Last aired\n|-\n| style=\"background:#000000;\"|\n| 1\n| 16\n| {{start date|2014|9|3|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2015|9|7|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#006600;\"|\n| 2\n| 15\n| {{start date|2016|1|5|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2016|4|19|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#E6B6D5;\"|\n| 3\n| 15\n| {{start date|2017|9|5|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2017|12|12|df=y}}\n|-\n|-\n| style=\"background:#0000FF;\"|\n| 4\n| 20\n| {{start date|2018|8|7|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2018|12|18|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#B11030;\"|\n| 5\n| 20\n|{{start date|2019|9|03|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2019|12|10|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#800080;\"|\n| 6\n| 20\n| {{start date|5 May 2020|df=y}}\n| {{end date|December 2020|df=y}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Development and production==\nOur school was commissioned by TwoFour and [[CBBC]] <ref>{{Citation|last=Catherine Booth Bible College.|title=CBBC.|date=1989|publisher=Office of Media Ministries|oclc=1057737839}}</ref> in September 2013, the series follows students from different primary schools and moving into secondary school. The series sees [[year 7]] students on their first year in a [[secondary school]] and follows the day-to-day life of children in school. The series uses a fly on the wall style camera system and is filmed over a whole year. Each series is filmed in a different school. The series are narrated by the teachers of the schools. The first series was made up of 16x30 minute episodes and ran for 15 weeks in 2014 with a special catch up episode airing in September 2015\n\nThe series was renewed for a second series and was made up of 15x30 minute episodes and the series aired in early 2017. In August prior to the third series a special episode aired in where 2 students from each school in series one and two met up and went to each other's schools to see what it's like. A third series has been ordered and will begin airing on 5 September 2017 and will again be made up of 15x30 minute episodes.\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episodes==\n===Series 1 (2014\u201315)===\nIt was filmed at [[Conyers' School|Conyers]] School in [[Yarm]] near [[Middlesbrough]]. It featured the Year Seven classes experiencing Secondary School and the challenges they may face in life such as multi skills\n\nOur School was first announced in early 2014, the series follows the same format as [[Educating (TV series)]] on Channel 4 which uses a fly on the wall cameras. The series follows 11 year 7's as they move up from primary school to secondary school and follows them on their first year. The first series was made up on 16x30 minute episodes and began broadcasting on 3 September 2014 and finished on 19 December 2019\n\nIn 2015 it was announced that a special episode would be added to the first series which aired on 7 September 2015 and was a catch-up episode which saw the cameras return to see on what had happened to the year 7's now year 8's since the series aired.\n\n*We are Year 7\n*New Horizons\n*Meet the Teachers\n*In Trouble \n*Finding Friends\n*Double Take\n*I Hate Quiet \n*Making Progress\n*Three Is a Magic Number\n*Behave Yourself\n*The Beautiful Game\n*Nothing to Be Scared Of\n*Love Is in the Air\n*Christmas is Coming\n*What Happened Next?\n\n===Series 2 (2016)===\nThis series is filmed at [[Greenwood Academy, Birmingham|Greenwood Academy]] in [[Castle Vale]] near [[Birmingham]].\n\nThe Second series of Our School began on 5 January 2016 and ran for 15 weeks with the final episode airing on 12 April 2016 and was retitled Our School 2 and followed the same style as series one.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MLKSP-CkVBY|title=Our School - Series 2: New Starts - BBC Documentary 2016|last=Cameron Decker|date=14 April 2016|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref><!--This is the trailer for the second series so do not remove-->\nThe Third series of Our School began on 5 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k31CKzM5UHY&list=PLK6EaM3xyUPfyqyEJxXhnl9eyga6c_W_A|title=Our School - Series 3: BBC Documentary 2017|last=Elvis Javier Mattos Villegas|date=5 September 2017|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref><!--This is the trailer for the second series so do not remove-->\n\nThe series was renewed for a third series and will air from September 2017. Before the launch of the third series there was one of special in which saw two students from series one and series two swap schools for a day and got to know the other students, the special aired in August 2017.\n\n*New Starts\t\n*On The Ball\t\n*Getting Ahead\t\n*Find Your Focus\t\n*Finding Friends\n*Change Your Ways\t\n*Going Forward,Stepping Back\t\n*You've Got A Friend\t\n*Who Am I?\t\n*My Camera Never Lies\t\n*Helping Out\t\n*We Can Be Heroes\t\n*Where The Heart Is\t\n*In It To Win It\t\n*Show Stopper\n\n===Series 3 (2017)===\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04gvnfv/credits|title=We Are Year 7, Series 1, Our School - Credits - BBC - CBBC|website=BBC}}</ref>\n\n*New Faces\t\n*True Colours\t\n*A Goal For Wayne\t\n*Meaty Matters\t\t\n*Just the Job\t\n*I Can't Do It...Yet\t\t\n*Show Me the Funny\t\t\n*You've Got A Friend\t\n*There's No i In Team\t\t\n*The Ghost of Firth Park\t\t\n*Swap the Teacher\t\n*Tricky Business\t\t\n*African Adventure\t\t\n*Moves Like Michael\t\t\n*Strictly Year Seven\n\n===Series 4 (2018)===\n*The New Boy\n*Laugh Out Loud\n*Give Us a Try\n*I'm Not Your Dude\n* It's Great Outdoors\n* A Piece of Cake\n*Something New\n*Frenemies \n*Try Being Me\n*Express Yourself\n*You Can't Win 'Em All\n*We're All Scottish \n*Deaducation\n*Back in the Day\n*Paws for Thought\n*Eyes on the Prize\n*In at the Deep End\n*Passion for Fashion\n*Edinburgh - Here We Come!\n*So This Is Christmas\n\n===Series 5 (2019)===\n*A Brand New Term\n*A Class Full of Chickens\n*When School Sucked\n*Here Comes Trouble\n*Plastic Not Fantastic\n*Lessons in Gunge\n*A Slice of Pizza\n*Face Your Fears\n*Partners in Crime\n*Our Scary Movie\n*Teaching Me Tidy\n*Leap of Faith\n*Vote for Me\n*Can't Play Will Play!\n*And Then They Were Eight\n*Would You Eat Frogs Legs\n*Keep Calm and Carry On\n*The Magic of Christmas \n*Get Your Act Together \n*Our School Rocks\n\n===Specials===\n*When Conyers Met Greenwood\n*One Last Term\n*Moving Day\n*Return To Firth Park\n*How We've Changed\n*Taking The Boys Out of Sheffield\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{BBC programme}}\n\n[[Category:2015 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:BBC high definition programmes]]\n[[Category:BBC Television programmes]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Our School|the South Korean documentary film|Our School (film)}}\n{{more citations needed|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Our School\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Entertainment]]<br />[[Documentary]]<br />[[Reality television]]\n| creator                  = [[BBC]]\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Cher Adamson<br />Chris Chapman<br />Matt Grosch<br>Jamie McLeish\n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| voices                   = Martin\n Thoburn (Series 1 & 2017 Special, 2018 Special, 2020 Special)<br> Trevor Evans (Series 2 & 2017 Special, 2018 Special, 2020 Special)<br> Martin Jones (Series 3 & 2018 Special) Ben Shore (2019 Special & 2020 Special)<br> Ewan Nicoll (Series 4 & 2019 Special, 2020 Special)<br>[[Shirley Ballas]] (Our School Summer Camp)<br> Helena Worth (Series 5 & 2020 Special)<br> Julie Kiley (Series 6)\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \"Our School\"\n| endtheme                 = \"Our School\"\n| composer                 = Sam Gale\n| country                  = [[United Kingdom]]\n| language                 = [[English language|English]] (UK)\n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = Kez Margrie<br />Richard Marson\n| producer                 = Vanessa Singh<br />Natasha Cox<br />Matt Grosch<br />Cher Adamson<br />Chris Chapman<br />Jamie McLeish\n| location                 = [[Conyers School]] (Series 1)<br />[[Greenwood Academy, Birmingham|Greenwood Academy]] (Series 2)<br />[[Firth Park Academy]] (Series 3)<br />[[Shawlands Academy]] (Series 4)\n[[Hawthorn High School]] (Series 5)<br />[[Ryburn Valley High School]] (Series 6)\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = Samdeep Singh Rana\n| camera                   = Multi camera<br />Dual cameras\n| runtime                  = 30 minutes\n| company                  = [[Twofour|TwoFour]]\n| distributor              = TwoFour\n| network                  = [[CBBC (TV channel)|CBBC]] (2014-present) <br>[[CBBC (TV channel)#CBBC HD|CBBC HD]] (2013-present)\n| picture_format           = [[High-definition television|HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format             = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2014|09|03|df=yes}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = \n| followed_by              = \n| related                  =\n| website                  = https://www.bbc.co.uk/cbbc/shows/our-school\n| production_website       = \n| num_series               = 6\n}}\n'''''Our School''''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[documentary]] [[reality television]] programme on [[CBBC]] which first aired on 3 September 2014 and has run for six series. It uses a [[fly on the wall]] format to show the everyday lives of the staff and pupils of secondary schools and follows children as they move from year 6 into year 7, each series is filmed in a different school.\n\n==Series overview==\n<!--Full linking is used for transclusion to main article-->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=2 rowspan=2|Series\n!rowspan=2|Episodes\n!colspan=2|Originally aired\n|-\n!First aired\n!Last aired\n|-\n| style=\"background:#000000;\"|\n| 1\n| 16\n| {{start date|2014|9|3|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2015|9|7|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#006600;\"|\n| 2\n| 15\n| {{start date|2016|1|5|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2016|4|19|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#E6B6D5;\"|\n| 3\n| 15\n| {{start date|2017|9|5|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2017|12|12|df=y}}\n|-\n|-\n| style=\"background:#0000FF;\"|\n| 4\n| 20\n| {{start date|2018|8|7|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2018|12|18|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#B11030;\"|\n| 5\n| 20\n|{{start date|2019|9|03|df=y}}\n| {{end date|2019|12|10|df=y}}\n|-\n| style=\"background:#800080;\"|\n| 6\n| 20\n| {{start date|5 May 2020|df=y}}\n| {{end date|December 2020|df=y}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Development and production==\nOur school was commissioned by TwoFour and [[CBBC]] <ref>{{Citation|last=Catherine Booth Bible College.|title=CBBC.|date=1989|publisher=Office of Media Ministries|oclc=1057737839}}</ref> in September 2013, the series follows students from different primary schools and moving into secondary school. The series sees [[year 7]] students on their first year in a [[secondary school]] and follows the day-to-day life of children in school. The series uses a fly on the wall style camera system and is filmed over a whole year. Each series is filmed in a different school. The series are narrated by the teachers of the schools. The first series was made up of 16x30 minute episodes and ran for 15 weeks in 2014 with a special catch up episode airing in September 2015\n\nThe series was renewed for a second series and was made up of 15x30 minute episodes and the series aired in early 2017. In August prior to the third series a special episode aired in where 2 students from each school in series one and two met up and went to each other's schools to see what it's like. A third series has been ordered and will begin airing on 5 September 2017 and will again be made up of 15x30 minute episodes.\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episodes==\n===Series 1 (2014\u201315)===\nIt was filmed at [[Conyers' School|Conyers]] School in [[Yarm]] near [[Middlesbrough]]. It featured the Year Seven classes experiencing Secondary School and the challenges they may face in life such as multi skills\n\nOur School was first announced in early 2014, the series follows the same format as [[Educating (TV series)]] on Channel 4 which uses a fly on the wall cameras. The series follows 11 year 7's as they move up from primary school to secondary school and follows them on their first year. The first series was made up on 16x30 minute episodes and began broadcasting on 3 September 2014 and finished on 19 December 2019\n\nIn 2015 it was announced that a special episode would be added to the first series which aired on 7 September 2015 and was a catch-up episode which saw the cameras return to see on what had happened to the year 7's now year 8's since the series aired.\n\n{{Episode table|background=#000000|overall=5|title=25|airdate=15|forceoverall=y|episodes\n\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |RTitle          = We are Year 7\n |OriginalAirDate = 3 September 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |RTitle          = New Horizons\n |OriginalAirDate = 10 September 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |RTitle          = Meet the Teachers\n |OriginalAirDate = 17 September\n|LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |RTitle          = In Trouble \n |OriginalAirDate = 24 September 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |RTitle          = Finding Friends\n |OriginalAirDate = 1 October 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School \n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |RTitle          = Double Take\n |OriginalAirDate = 8 October 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |RTitle          = Goals\n |OriginalAirDate = 15 October 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Educating Manchester\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |RTitle          = I Hate Quiet \n |OriginalAirDate = 22 October 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 9\n |RTitle          = Making Progress\n |OriginalAirDate = 29 October 2014 \n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Our School\n |EpisodeNumber   = 10\n |RTitle          = Three Is a Magic Number\n |OriginalAirDate = 5 November 2014\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\